### Analysis of the Main Target Image:

- **Count & Layers:** The structure consists of 6 building blocks arranged in a multi-layered configuration.
- **Spatial Relationships:**
  - Two yellow semi-circular blocks are placed at the top, side by side.
  - Below these, there are two red C-shaped blocks positioned back-to-back.
  - Supporting these is an orange cylindrical block standing vertically.
  - At the base, there are two orange triangular blocks lying flat on either side of the cylinder.

### Selection of Required Blocks from the Dictionary:

- **Block Indices:**
  - Yellow Semi-Circular Block: Index 10
  - Red C-Shaped Block: Index 3
  - Orange Cylindrical Block: Index 8
  - Orange Triangular Block: Index 15

### Assembly Order:

{
   Step1: Move block with index 15 (orange triangular block) to the left base position.
   Step2: Move block with index 15 (orange triangular block) to the right base position.
   Step3: Move block with index 8 (orange cylindrical block) to the center vertical position.
   Step4: Move block with index 3 (red C-shaped block) to the left middle position.
   Step5: Move block with index 3 (red C-shaped block) to the right middle position.
   Step6: Move block with index 10 (yellow semi-circular block) to the left top position.
   Step7: Move block with index 10 (yellow semi-circular block) to the right top position.
}
